tool_description: A multipurpose API that includes many image, video, and audio operations. Please see https://ko-fi.com/mizabot if you'd like premium features on the Discord bot itself!
title: Miza

api_list.name: Retrieve file
api_list.description: Retrieves a file hosted by the server. This link is usually obtained by replacing the /p/ path in the /merge and /edit endpoint responses with /f/ or /d/. The request fails if the file requested does not exist or has been deleted.
api_list.code:
import requests

url = "https://miza.p.rapidapi.com/d/{path}"

headers = {
    "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
    "X-RapidAPI-Host": "miza.p.rapidapi.com"
}

response = requests.get(url, headers=headers)

print(response.json())

api_list.name: Delete file
api_list.description: Permanently removes an uploaded file, rendering it unable to be retrieved or edited. This immediately cuts all links including pending downloads as well as internal filesystem and cloud links, and all cached and backup copies of file data on the servers. The original edit key for the file must be provided in order for this endpoint to function.

api_list.name: Merge file chunks
api_list.description: Merges file chunks and finalises their cache and retrieve status on the server. Must be called to make the file visible, even if only one chunk was uploaded. The x-index field in this case specifies the highest index file that was uploaded. Returns the edit link to the file, which is no longer retrievable afterwards, and should be saved elsewhere if edit access is desired. For compatibility with the website this endpoint returns the /p/ url which links to the preview link. To retrieve or edit the file, replace this with /d/ or /edit/ respectively.

api_list.name: Edit file
api_list.description:
Edits an existing file hosted by the server. The file's ID and key must be provided in the URL as path and query respectively. This request must be preceded by one or more /upload_chunk requests, which specify the new file data
 Like the /merge endpoint, the name and final index of the uploaded chunks must be provided. The old file (if applicable) is permanently removed during this process, and will no longer be accessible.

api_list.name: Upload chunk
api_list.description:
Uploads a single chunk of a file. If you want a simple service that does not require a lot of redundancy, this only needs to be called once per file, with the entire file as input. Otherwise, files may be cut into sections, with index specifying which chunk is which.
Must be followed up by an appropriate /merge or /edit request in order for this uploaded file to be accessed, even if only one chunk is uploaded. Otherwise it will be deleted if left for more than a day.

api_list.name: IP address check
api_list.description: Retrieves the host (server) and remote (your) IP addresses. A fast and responsive endpoint that is also handy for checking whether the service is online.
api_list.code:
import requests

url = "https://miza.p.rapidapi.com/ip"

headers = {
    "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
    "X-RapidAPI-Host": "miza.p.rapidapi.com"
}

response = requests.get(url, headers=headers)

print(response.json())

api_list.name: Song trimming/extending
api_list.description:
Trims a song or video, outputting as a URL (similar to the concatenation function). Like the output from concat, one must send a GET request to the URL returned in order to retrieve the actual output.
Specify trim start and end after the URL, optionally omitting them by replacing them with an empty string or dash (-). Accepts input in number of seconds, as well as time formats such as *2h30m* or *1:53:30*.
If the trim end passes the end of the song, it will automatically be extended by looping back from the beginning. This is *much* faster than concatenating multiple copies of the same song, as it skips re-encoding every single copy, allowing it to produce 10-hour extensions of songs or videos in seconds. Output format can additionally be specified after trim end.
See https://mizabot.xyz/downloader for more info as well as test usage of this endpoint.

api_list.name: Song search
api_list.description:
Searches for a song from popular song platforms.
The API will search YouTube for the item by default. Prepend *scsearch:* to the search term to specify a search from SoundCloud, *spsearch:* for Spotify, or *bcsearch:* for BandCamp.
Unlike all other endpoints provided by this API, this endpoint can actually be used infinitely free of charge or quota. Simply direct your request directly to [http://i.mizabot.xyz/ytdl?search=](http://i.mizabot.xyz/ytdl?search=) instead of rapidapi's forwarded URL. This may be done for all other endpoints too, however there will be a rate limit in place.

api_list.name: Song concatenation
api_list.description:
Joins one or more audio or video files into a single file.
Inputs are specified by URLs specified by query parameters "u1", "u2", etc. These URLs may be playlists, which will perform the concat operation on all contained tracks.
Output format supports most video and audio formats. See https://mizabot.xyz/downloader for list of available formats, as well as test usage of this API.
May or may not be the same input format, codec, or framerate/resolution/aspect ratio (if it is a video), but will take much longer to provide a response compared to the download endpoint, because it must finish all conversion before it can begin streaming.
Redirects to a URL which will return the output file. This download link will be reusable, but temporary.

api_list.name: Playlist extraction
api_list.description: Produces information on all songs in a playlist (YouTube, Spotify, SoundCloud, etc), with much faster response time than most other available tools. Currently O(1) for YouTube, O(log n) for Spotify, and O(log n) for SoundCloud. See [this article](http://i.mizabot.xyz/f/Bc9AUlCRkA) for the algorithm behind the YouTube playlists specifically.

api_list.name: Upload chunk
api_list.description:
Uploads a single chunk of a file. If you want a simple service that does not require a lot of redundancy, this only needs to be called once per file, with the entire file as input. Otherwise, files may be cut into sections, with index specifying which chunk is which.
Must be followed up by an appropriate /merge or /edit request in order for this uploaded file to be accessed, even if only one chunk is uploaded. Otherwise it will be deleted if left for more than a day.
